NAME
  loopabull

SYNOPSIS
  loopabull CONFIG

DESCRIPTION
  loopabull is an event loop driven Ansible playbook execution engine

  loopabull is generally meant to be executed as a daemon process via
  systemd(1), however it can be run interactively by passing the path to a
  configuration file as the only argument.

EXAMPLE

  $ loopabull /etc/loopabull.yml

SEE ALSO
  ansible(1), ansible-playbook(1)